            <p align="left">Curriculum Vitae for the Minister of Labour and Social Inclusion</p>
<p align="left"><b>Personal data</b></p><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"></b>
<ul type="disc">
<li>Family name: Hanssen </li>
<li>First names: Bjarne Håkon </li>
<li>Date of birth: 1 November 1962 </li>
<li>Family: married, 4 children</li></ul>
<table border="0">
<tbody>
<tr valign="top">
<td colspan="2">
<p align="left" colspan="2"><b>Political Assignments</b></p></td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>2008-2009</td>
<td>Minister of Health and Care Services and Minister of Labour and Social Inclusion</td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<p>2005–2008:</p></td>
<td>Minister of Labour and Social Inclusion</td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<p>2003–2005:</p></td>
<td>Head of the Labour Party’s Working Group for European Debate</td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<p>2001–2005:</p></td>
<td>Member of the Storting, the Norwegian Parliament, representing the county of Nord-Trøndelag. Member of the Standing Committee on Social Affairs</td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<p>2001–2005:</p></td>
<td>Member of the Labour Party’s Leading Group </td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<p>2000–2001:</p></td>
<td>Minister of Agriculture</td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>1997–2001:</td>
<td>
<p align="left">Member of the Storting, representing Nord-Trøndelag. Member of the Standing Committee on Business and Industry</p></td></tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>1995–1997:</td>
